about.summary: Fit linear and generalized linear mixed models with various extensions, including zero-inflation. The models are fitted using maximum likelihood estimation via 'TMB' (Template Model Builder). Random effects are assumed to be Gaussian on the scale of the linear predictor and are integrated out using the Laplace approximation. Gradients are calculated using automatic differentiation.

name: r-glmmtmb
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-glmmtmb
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/glmmTMB_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/glmmTMB/glmmTMB_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: b582ac41fb4390146f1446c6629fec40c6c9c125f99083602f091dc60f0ebd69

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-matrix
    - r-rcppeigen
    - r-tmb >=1.7.14
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_18.9000
    - r-nlme
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-matrix
    - r-rcppeigen
    - r-tmb >=1.7.14
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_18.9000
    - r-nlme

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('glmmTMB')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('glmmTMB')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/glmmTMB
  license: AGPL-3
  summary: Fit linear and generalized linear mixed models with various extensions, including zero-inflation. The models are fitted using maximum likelihood estimation
    via 'TMB' (Template Model Builder). Random effects are assumed to be Gaussian on the scale of the linear predictor and are integrated out using the Laplace approximation.
    Gradients are calculated using automatic differentiation.
  license_family: AGPL
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/AGPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ccwang002
